The evidence with the title 'Why the Clean Tech Boom went bust | wired ' says Jan 20, 2012  ... By 2008 , the year after Doerr's speech, it had leaped to $4.1 billion. And the federal government followed . Through a mix of loans, subsidies, and tax breaks, it directed roughly $ 44.5 billion into the sector between late 2009 and late 2011. Avarice , altruism, and policy had aligned to fuel a spectacular boom. 
